ty, she deciphers how long-cherished imaginaries of holiness broker bonds of revolutionary sacrifice, reconfigure national sites of sacred territory, and pose sectarian threats to security and order. A study of tradition and nationhood at their limits, The Political Lives of Saints shows that Coptic Orthodoxy is a core domain of minoritarian regulation and authoritarian rule, powerfully reversing the recurrent thesis of its impending extinction in the Arab Muslim world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChristianity and other religionsxIslam. 0aChristianity and other religions-Islam. 0aChristianityzEgypt. 0aChristianity-Egypt. 0aCoptic Christian saintszEgypt. 0aCoptic Christian saints-Egypt. 0aCoptic Church-Egypt. 0aCoptszEgyptxPolitics and government. 0aCoptszEgyptxSocial conditionsy21st century. 0aCopts-Politics and government. 0aIslam and politicszEgypt. 0aIslam and politics-Egypt. 0aIslamxRelationsxChristianity. 0aIslam-Relations-Christianity. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDTL Humanities 2020z978311073776908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311066767740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520970120?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520970120423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520970120/original  a978-3-11-066767-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-073776-9  DTL Humanities 2020b2020  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles